		<outline text="June 2004" created="Tue, 01 Jun 2004 05:00:02 GMT">
			<outline text="June 30" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2004 05:00:01 GMT">
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://developer.apple.com/macosx/rendezvous/&quot;&gt;Apple&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;Rendezvous is now available on Windows 2000 and XP.&quot;" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2004 21:10:08 GMT" name="aHrefhttpdeveloperapplecommacosxrendezvousappleaRendezvousIsNowAvailableOnWindows2000AndXp" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://wmf.editthispage.com/2004/06/30&quot;&gt;Wes Felter&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;I'd like to remind everyone that Rendezvous libraries for Linux, Windows, and Java have existed for months.&quot;" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2004 00:47:00 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;img src=&quot;http://images.scripting.com/archiveScriptingCom/2004/06/30/sixColorApple.gif&quot; width=&quot;55&quot; height=&quot;58&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; hspace=&quot;15&quot; vspace=&quot;5&quot; alt=&quot;A picture named sixColorApple.gif&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://daringfireball.net/2004/06/dashboard_vs_konfabulator&quot;&gt;Daring Fireball dismisses&lt;/a&gt; the idea that Apple ripped off Konfabulator. There actually is some validity to the developer complaint, and there's a lot to be said for licking your wounds quietly esp when you produce software of great utility but limited depth. What's good is that developers are starting to care about other developers. That's important. Create strategies together that build on each others' strengths. There's no power in complaining about Apple, of course they can add features to their OS, esp ones that link back to the Macintosh of 1984. But if you all viewed the Mac OS as a collaborative development platform, you could market your stuff independent of Apple. Now that would be &lt;i&gt;much&lt;/i&gt; more revolutionary than a pretty collection of useful widgets. (Which has been done before over and over ad nauseum.)" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2004 20:59:27 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://davenet.scripting.com/1997/05/07/Programmers&quot;&gt;1997&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;My pitch to programmers, which is far more revolutionary than any programming language or operating system can be, is to look for understanding where you find it, work with people you want to work with, and don't waste time with people who won't listen and aren't grounded in the truth.&quot;" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2004 21:05:27 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://wedding.buzzword.com/picture$42&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://images.scripting.com/archiveScriptingCom/2004/06/30/bug.jpg&quot; width=&quot;85&quot; height=&quot;39&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; hspace=&quot;15&quot; vspace=&quot;5&quot; alt=&quot;A picture named bug.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;A few days ago Rogers &lt;a href=&quot;http://archive.scripting.com/2004/06/24#When:3:48:29PM&quot;&gt;asked&lt;/a&gt; what stories were lurking in the 3000-plus websites that used to be hosted on weblogs.com. Well I had trouble sleeping, so I started poking around, and came across this &lt;a href=&quot;http://wedding.buzzword.com/discuss/msgReader$109?mode=day&quot;&gt;site with pictures&lt;/a&gt; of a &lt;a href=&quot;http://wedding.buzzword.com/picture$42&quot;&gt;hippie&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://wedding.buzzword.com/discuss/msgReader$106?mode=day&quot;&gt;wedding&lt;/a&gt; in Oregon. Interesting. One of the guys looks just like Jake Savin. Oh wow, that's Jake's &lt;a href=&quot;http://wedding.buzzword.com/picture$45&quot;&gt;brother&lt;/a&gt;. He's getting married. There's Jake! Wow. Lots of pictures, and people wrote their stories about the wedding on the blog, including &lt;a href=&quot;http://wedding.buzzword.com/picture$38&quot;&gt;Jake's mom&lt;/a&gt;, who gave us some &lt;i&gt;really&lt;/i&gt; good advice when my dad was sick (she's a doctor). There you go Rogers, a story. &lt;a href=&quot;http://wedding.buzzword.com/discuss/msgReader$105?mode=day&quot;&gt;Real&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://wedding.buzzword.com/discuss/msgReader$108?mode=day&quot;&gt;people&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Thu, 01 Jul 2004 03:31:05 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/business/3854605.stm&quot;&gt;BBC&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;The US Federal Reserve has raised interest rates by a quarter percentage point, in a widely-anticipated move.&quot;" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2004 18:41:23 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Now some of the mail has been very gratifying, coming from Republicans, who also dislike Moore, and now seem a little more interested in what I think about the war and related issues. That's how Moore can do some good, we can find the common ground that connects us, as Americans. Basic fact -- we have to live with each other. Moore doesn't offer us a way to do that. By extrapolation, Republicans with minds should openly distance themselves from the right-wing anti-intellectuals (some of whom run this country, btw). It's time to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/images/archiveScriptingCom/2004/05/31/think.gif&quot;&gt;think&lt;/a&gt;, how are we going to avoid a debacle like the election of 2000? Seriously, we're headed for a replay. " created="Wed, 30 Jun 2004 18:58:29 GMT" type="outline"/>
