				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ananova.com/entertainment/story/sm_807684.html?menu=entertainment&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://images.scripting.com/archiveScriptingCom/2004/06/30/moore.jpg&quot; width=&quot;45&quot; height=&quot;50&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; hspace=&quot;15&quot; vspace=&quot;5&quot; alt=&quot;A picture named moore.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;I'm getting a lot of interesting mail about the &lt;a href=&quot;http://archive.scripting.com/2004/06/30#mooresTactics&quot;&gt;piece&lt;/a&gt; about Michael Moore below. This stuff should be on blogs somewhere so other people can read it. I can't put up a comment thread because there are also some really abusive opinions in the mix. If you didn't call me a four-letter word, it's not abusive. And you can be a former reader, no problemmo, I already have a lot of readers, I can afford to lose some. &quot;;-&gt;&quot; " created="Wed, 30 Jun 2004 16:54:37 GMT" type="outline"/>
