				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://lab.msdn.microsoft.com/productfeedback/&quot;&gt;Microsoft opened&lt;/a&gt; up their bug reporting system for Visual Studio. You can report a bug, which isn't exactly a new feature, but you can review their bug database, which is quite unusual. They also came out with a development &lt;a href=&quot;http://lab.msdn.microsoft.com/express/&quot;&gt;environment&lt;/a&gt; for beginning programmers called Visual Studio Express, and sample apps, including an RSS 2.0 &lt;a href=&quot;http://weblogs.asp.net/danielfe/archive/2004/06/29/168449.aspx&quot;&gt;screen saver&lt;/a&gt; in C#. " created="Wed, 30 Jun 2004 11:16:12 GMT" type="outline"/>
