				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://movies.yahoo.com/shop?d=hv&amp;cf=info&amp;id=1808467110&amp;intl=us&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://images.scripting.com/archiveScriptingCom/2004/06/27/grams.jpg&quot; width=&quot;65&quot; height=&quot;81&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; hspace=&quot;15&quot; vspace=&quot;5&quot; alt=&quot;A picture named grams.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Recent movies: &lt;a href=&quot;http://movies.yahoo.com/shop?d=hv&amp;cf=info&amp;id=1808435938&amp;intl=us&quot;&gt;Lost In Translation&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://movies.yahoo.com/shop?d=hv&amp;id=1808428703&amp;cf=info&quot;&gt;In America&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://movies.yahoo.com/shop?d=hv&amp;cf=info&amp;id=1808467110&amp;intl=us&quot;&gt;21 Grams&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://movies.yahoo.com/shop?d=hv&amp;cf=info&amp;id=1808467470&amp;intl=us&quot;&gt;Fog of War&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://movies.yahoo.com/shop?d=hv&amp;cf=info&amp;id=1808403165&amp;intl=us&quot;&gt;Big Fish&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://movies.yahoo.com/shop?d=hv&amp;cf=info&amp;id=1808405428&amp;intl=us&quot;&gt;Finding Nemo&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://movies.yahoo.com/shop?d=hv&amp;cf=info&amp;id=1800113383&amp;intl=us&quot;&gt;The Ruling Class&lt;/a&gt;. Listed roughly in the order that I liked them. The last three were repeats, Big Fish was great to see a second time, but Finding Nemo seemed really shallow (the turtles were great of course) and The Ruling Class, a great movie for its day, is finally dated. Lost In Translation, which I had not seen, deserved all its accolade. A gorgeous flowing light story, more of a mood piece, richly photographed, emotionally grabbing, sweet. I wish the character with the bad heart in 21 Grams didn't smoke, that really hurt to watch. In America, just a nice movie. Etc etc. " created="Sun, 27 Jun 2004 22:00:52 GMT" name="" type="outline"/>
