				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.goupstate.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20040625/APF/406250771&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;Al-Qaida-linked terror groups and their sympathizers have in recent months made a big splash on the Internet, making it their communications channel of choice. They're benefiting from free discussion boards, e-mail accounts and other online forums for propaganda, recruitment, fund-raising and even planning.&quot;" created="Sat, 26 Jun 2004 01:37:28 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="Scott Rosenberg: &lt;a href=&quot;http://blogs.salon.com/0000014/2004/06/25.html#a630&quot;&gt;Blogs, bosses and bucks&lt;/a&gt;." created="Sat, 26 Jun 2004 01:46:22 GMT" type="outline"/>
