				<outline text="&lt;img src=&quot;http://images.scripting.com/archiveScriptingCom/2004/06/23/hope.jpg&quot; width=&quot;150&quot; height=&quot;253&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; align=&quot;right&quot; hspace=&quot;15&quot; vspace=&quot;5&quot; alt=&quot;A picture named hope.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wired.com/news/culture/0,1284,63953,00.html?tw=wn_tophead_5&quot;&gt;Wired&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;What was decried as the death of a blog universe when Dave Winer shut down free blog host Weblogs.com turned out to be little more than a four-day server outage surrounded by a heck of a flame war.&quot;" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2004 16:19:41 GMT" type="outline"/>
