				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.kottke.org/03/05/jason-rules-nyc-subway&quot;&gt;Jason Kottke&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;Get the hell out of my way, I'm coming through.&quot;" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2004 18:06:27 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://weblog.infoworld.com/foster/2004/06/22.html#a118&quot;&gt;Ed Foster&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;In a recent weblog item, I talked about the owner of a new PC who had to pay $149 for Dell support to tell her how to change a default setting in Outlook. This spurred quite a debate among readers about just who was to blame.&quot;" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2004 11:00:49 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://cadenhead.org/workbench/2004/06/21.html#a1809&quot;&gt;Rogers Cadenhead&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;When Buzzword.Com was launched last week, I had a feeling that the good news about restoring service to Weblogs.Com users would have more trouble getting around than the original, over-the-top reports of a blogger's 9/11.&quot;" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2004 06:07:06 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://archive.scripting.com/2002/06/22&quot;&gt;Two years ago&lt;/a&gt;, a site &lt;a href=&quot;http://everybody.blogs.it/&quot;&gt;hosted&lt;/a&gt; by Paolo Valdemarin with get well messages. Last week's shitstorm exactly coincided with my health failure two years ago. Maybe the echo chamber of the blogosphere is deeper than we previously thought?" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2004 06:49:48 GMT" type="outline"/>
