				<outline text="According to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.bletter.com/abcedmindedness/2004/06/lyris-does-rss.html&quot;&gt;Ray Daly&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.lyris.com/products/listmanager/beta_news.html&quot;&gt;Lyris&lt;/a&gt; is adding &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.lyris.com/lm_help/8.0/index_h1.html?rss.html&quot;&gt;RSS support&lt;/a&gt; to their &quot;great email list manager software.&quot;" created="Tue, 15 Jun 2004 23:05:01 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.cybersaps.org/categories/cyberSaps/2004/06/15.html#a1795&quot;&gt;Steve Hooker offers&lt;/a&gt; free Manila hosting to any weblogs.com author. Steve is a pleasure to work with, a real pro. There are other such offers in the works. Note, we won't have to wait until July 1 to do these transfers, and I will install redirects, so links won't break. " created="Tue, 15 Jun 2004 22:49:12 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="No question, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.theregister.co.uk/2004/06/15/winer_weblog_wipeout/&quot;&gt;Orlowski is writing&lt;/a&gt; comedy. I laughed five times reading this. Especially the parts about BloggerCon. &quot;The only way I would attend such a conference is with a bottle in front of me or a frontal lobotomy.&quot;" created="Tue, 15 Jun 2004 22:57:31 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.teachnology.org/2004/06/15&quot;&gt;Dan Mitchell&lt;/a&gt; takes issue with Orlowski's piece. BTW, the free hosting was for four years, not two." created="Wed, 16 Jun 2004 01:26:01 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mozilla.org/press/mozilla-2004-06-15.html&quot;&gt;Press release&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;The Mozilla Foundation today announced the immediate availability of a new preview release of its next generation web browser, Mozilla Firefox 0.9.&quot;" created="Tue, 15 Jun 2004 20:28:24 GMT" type="outline"/>
